text: José Félix Quirós (1811, San Miguel, El Salvador - 1883, San Miguel) was President of El Salvador 3 - 7 February 1848 and 1 March - 3 May 1851.http://www.rulers.org/rule.html He served as Vice President of Doroteo Vasconcelos from February 1848 to April 1851, and Vice President of Gerardo Barrios from February 1860 to October 1863.http://www.redicces.org.sv/jspui/bitstream/10972/1810/1/Nociones%20de%20Historia%20de%20El%20Salvador.%201920.%20Rafael%20Reyes.pdf ==References== Category:Presidents of El Salvador Category:Vice Presidents of El Salvador Category:1811 births Category:1883 deaths Category:19th-century Salvadoran people
title: José Félix Quirós
